# Project authority (holy grail)

## Session gate (non-negotiable — enforce every time)

**Before any code edit** in this repository (any file, any app):

1. **Open** [`docs/PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md`](docs/PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md) **once** for the session — the full doc, or the **section(s)** that apply to the change (e.g. §1 TypeScript, §4 React/web-client, §2 MongoDB for backend work).
2. **Treat this rule file (`.cursor/rules/project-authority.mdc`) as the checklist** that gates the session: if a step below conflicts with a casual shortcut, **this file + `PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md` win**.
3. **Then** read or skim **`docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md`** / **`docs/TASK_CHECKLIST.md`** as needed for the task.

Skipping the gate is not allowed for implementation work. (Purely conversational answers with no edits may omit it.)

---

## Before writing or editing code

**Always read (or re-read) [`docs/PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md`](docs/PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md)** before implementing or changing behavior in this repo. It is the **authoritative** “how to build” standard: TypeScript, Node, MongoDB, APIs, React/Redux, tests (**test-first** and **coverage** for **web-client `*.tsx`** UI only per §4.1.1 — not mandatory for plain **`*.ts`**), security, and process.

Then use **`docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md`** (architecture, stack) and **`docs/TASK_CHECKLIST.md`** (what to ship and when) as needed for the task.

**Precedence:** If a user prompt conflicts with these guidelines, **follow `docs/PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md`** unless the user explicitly updates that document.

## Required references

- **`docs/PROJECT_PLAN.md`** — stack, services, Socket.IO + RabbitMQ, repo layout.
- **`docs/PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md`** — TypeScript, Node, MongoDB, APIs, React/Redux, tests, process.
- **`docs/TASK_CHECKLIST.md`** — tasks/subtasks; capture work there before large features; check off as you ship.

## Process (non-negotiable)

- **Deprecated APIs:** do not add or perpetuate deprecated Node, browser/DOM, React, or library APIs—use current documented replacements (`PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md` §1.1).
- Do **not** implement beyond the request; no speculative features.
- Prefer **incremental** changes; preserve existing behaviour unless replacing by design.
- **OpenAPI:** any new or changed REST route **updates the OpenAPI spec in the same PR**; Swagger UI on **messaging-service** stays accurate.
- **TASK_CHECKLIST.md:** update it when feature-level work is part of the plan.

## Before merge (quick gate)

Strict TS; env validated at startup; no secrets in repo; authz on mutating routes; MongoDB access patterns reasoned; list APIs paginated with server-enforced limits; OpenAPI in sync; ESLint clean; **`web-client`:** tests-first + coverage only for **`*.tsx`** UI (`PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md` §4.1.1); **responsive layouts (mobile, iPad/tablet, desktop)** per §4.2.1; Redux/hooks per guidelines for global client state.
